node.text:
A lot of people ask what my “off season” training will look like. Right now, and for a couple more days it looks like almost nothing. The most I’ve done since Games are body building sessions…..I have done one, ONE cardio piece. The most athletic thing I’ve done this past month is seeing how far i can stretch my stomach. Honestly, competitive eating could be a bright future for me😹 But the next stage I truly believe should be about having fun and doing things purely for the fact that I WANT to. I see tons of athletes doing just that right now, I’m just playing catch up 💁🏼‍♀️ I see other people doing the things they love. I see people choosing to go on runs everyday — the psychopaths of the world. Other chose to do cycling classes or yoga or things they usually don’t get to enjoy in the middle of the season. But me - i want to PLAY. I want to throw around odd object toys like the pig 👆🏼👆🏼I want to push sleds, throw sandbags, continue to hit “bro sessions”, dumbbells, kettlebells…just all of the toys. And yes, I’ll probably jump on a bike here and there so my heart doesn’t explode when I finally get back around to a lot of high intensity sessions 💀 so here’s to the next stage of the off season 👏🏼 The food, the relaxation, the reflection, the truly lazy days, the “meh not today” mind set, and the “healing stage” have been amazing. But I’m ready to play now 😈 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For everyone still checking in on me and my ankle issue - thank you 🤍 I have a plan set in place but still waiting on some big decisions for the future and will update everyone once I get everything finalized! xoxo 💋

node.text:
*Insert inspirational quote about how everything happens for a reason and I’ll come back stronger next year…* ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The truth is I’m livid. I’m devastated that my weekend got cut short because of an injury, that in reality, is stupid ☹️ Yes, there’s always next year, but I wanted this year. Yes I’ll come back stronger but I’m strong now. And yes this will fuel the fire - but my fire has been burning for the past 3 years with injuries and unfortunate circumstances - it’ll just make next year that much sweeter🤪 But yes, big things coming 👏🏼 THANK YOU to everyone who’s sent words of encouragement and love. I couldn’t ask for better cheering squad - you guys are amazing and I am thriving off of your love and good vibes. 🤍 and CONGRATS to all of the amazing athletes who competed this weekend 🥰

✔️great taste ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
